ğŸ”¹ 3. Set Interface
> Unordered
> No duplicates

Common Classes:
* HashSet â€“ uses hash table, fastest
* LinkedHashSet â€“ maintains insertion order
* TreeSet â€“ sorted order (uses TreeMap internally)



ğŸ”¹ 4. Queue Interface
> FIFO (First-In-First-Out)
> Used for processing tasks

Common Classes:
* PriorityQueue â€“ elements processed based on priority
* ArrayDeque â€“ double-ended queue


ğŸ”¹ 5. Map Interface
> Stores key-value pairs
> No duplicate keys

Common Classes:
* HashMap â€“ no order
* LinkedHashMap â€“ insertion order
* TreeMap â€“ sorted by keys
* Hashtable â€“ synchronized


  ğŸ” Summary Table:

| Interface | Implementation | Features                 |
